Pushing your edge… I did a thing 🧘‍♀️ ~ #certifiedyogainstructor 💖 Movement has always been a part of my life as a former #gymnast and sprinter #trackandfield, though there have been ups and downs. Once yoga entered my life , even more importantly the mental aspects of a practice were more apparent and grew from there. During #psychiatry residency, I had the privilege of working with various wonderful human beings, at various points in life. I started to combine therapy, medication when needed, yoga practice recs, #meditation and #journaling among other things. The #benefits of a combination of things that act on our mind and body cannot be understated. Everyone needs something different, but was born the idea of a #holisticmentalhealth practice. I’ve now completed my #200houryogateachertraining along with my #100hourmeditationteachertraining and look forward to bringing one of my dreams into reality. Stay tuned for the next step 💕💕💕 #wellness #mentalhealth #holisticpsychiatry #athleta #yogawear @athleta 

Adding— sometimes as in #yinyoga and life, we need to push our edge. I kept daydreaming about finishing yoga teacher training, one day I had to tell myself, you need to start doing on that dream 💕💕 #thepowerofshe #mentalhealthawarenessmonth #brainhealth #powerofshe
